    • Method Detail

      • save

        Model save(Model instance)
    throws java.sql.SQLException
        The save functionality persists an object instance to the database. Only a current business object instance with a relevant change in its process status aspect or a newly created business object instance will be persisted.
        Parameters:
        instance - - the object instance being saved
        Returns:
        the instance with updated technical id (== database entry id)
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - sql exception

      • saveList

        ModelList saveList(ModelList instanceList)
            throws java.sql.SQLException
        The saveList functionality persists a list of business object instances to the database. Only a current business object instance with a relevant change in its process status aspect or a newly created business object instance will be persisted.
        Parameters:
        instanceList - list of objects to save
        Returns:
        a list of instances with updated technical id value (== database entry id)
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - sql exception
